File: A soccer ball seen on a pitch. Pixabay/jarmoluk LONDON - The number of postponed English Premier League games continues to increase. Newcastle United’s match at Southampton is the latest fixture to be called off due to Covid-19 and injuries. The Magpies’ clash at Everton on Thursday was also called off. A total of 18 games have now been postponed in the Premier League since the start of December. Liverpool’s match at Chelsea on Sunday evening is hanging in the balance as the Reds players await tests indicating whether the virus is present. Despite a growing number of Covid-19 cases and injuries leading to depleted squads, the Premier League and EFL clubs chose to fulfil their festive fixtures.